Change Management is no task to be performed on the fly
.stk-mgw4q57{margin-bottom:0px !important}.stk-mgw4q57 .stk--svg-wrapper .stk--inner-svg svg:last-child,.stk-mgw4q57 .stk--svg-wrapper .stk--inner-svg svg:last-child :is(g,path,rect,polygon,ellipse){fill:var(--theme-palette-color-4,#0c5794) !important}
There are inconvenient truths that are only told reluctantly in most projects. One of the biggest is that even if veiled, changes are inherent to every project and will assume an independent existence if not managed​​.
.stk-wikksp8{margin-bottom:0px !important}.stk-wikksp8 .stk--svg-wrapper .stk--inner-svg svg:last-child,.stk-wikksp8 .stk--svg-wrapper .stk--inner-svg svg:last-child :is(g,path,rect,polygon,ellipse){fill:var(--theme-palette-color-4,#0c5794) !important}
One of the great paradoxes in project management. The reasons why most projects fail are known but despite this knowledge projects continue to face challenges and ultimately fail despite this awareness.
.stk-89uiaf5{margin-bottom:0px !important}.stk-89uiaf5 .stk--svg-wrapper .stk--inner-svg svg:last-child,.stk-89uiaf5 .stk--svg-wrapper .stk--inner-svg svg:last-child :is(g,path,rect,polygon,ellipse){fill:var(--theme-palette-color-4,#0c5794) !important}
It’s a people’s game. Effective change management concentrates the willingness of the people and maintains a certain spirit. Knowing that there is more to ‘true’ and ‘false’ levers your success​​.

Alexandre Rezende
